    "created_at": "2015-01-05T21:35:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-05T21:35:05Z",
    "body": "But RangeTo doesn't represent a range that starts from zero, it's a range that has no lower bound, and therefore cannot be iterated in a forward direction.\n\nOne possibility is to extract the method \"next_back\" from \"DoubleEndedIterator\" into a separate trait: \"ReverseIterator\" or \"BackIterator\", and \"DoubleEndedIterator\" is then equivalent to \"Iterator + BackIterator\".\n\nNow, \"Range\" can implement \"DoubleEndedIterator\", \"RangeFrom\" can implement \"Iterator\", and \"RangeTo\" can implement \"BackIterator\". Finally, the \"Rev\" function is extended to work on all iterators, such that Rev(Iterator) => BackIterator, Rev(BackIterator) => Iterator, and Rev(DoubleEndedIterator) => DoubleEndedIterator.\n\nThis would allow iteration of RangeTo but only in the reverse direction.\n",
